===Etymology===
A word of uncertain formation. The first element is ultimately identical with {{term|know}}, but the second is obscure (neither Old Norse {{term|-leikr}} nor Old English {{term|-lac|-lāċ}} would have given ''-leche'' as found in the earliest Middle English citations).
* <span style="font-size:85%;">The noun originally provided a counterpart to the now-obsolete verb ''to knowledge'', but was very early adapted to be the noun equivalent of {{term|know}}.</span>

